deployment_id.description: The ID of the deployment to evolve. If omitted, the latest deployment will be used.

exclude_external_mcps.description: The external MCP servers, identified by slug, to exclude from the new deployment when cloning a previous deployment.
example: Laborum aut non fugiat itaque aut.

exclude_functions.description: The functions, identified by slug, to exclude from the new deployment when cloning a previous deployment.
example: Dicta placeat aut aspernatur et sunt ut.
Similique vitae reprehenderit maiores aut aut dolorum.

exclude_packages.description: The packages to exclude from the new deployment when cloning a previous deployment.

non_blocking.description: If true, the deployment will be created in non-blocking mode where the request will return immediately and the deployment will proceed asynchronously.

upsert_functions.description: The tool functions to upsert in the new deployment.

upsert_packages.description: The packages to upsert in the new deployment.
